cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses rule-based information extraction, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields in computer science, including databases (cs.DB), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on information extraction and the use of mappings to handle incomplete data, cs.DB and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses computational properties such as query enumeration, which further supports the likelihood of cs.DB as a relevant sub-category.
